data.description:
To schedule a viewing or for more information, please contact Bryan at 435-531-0500 or email at beckyhyde57@gmail.com.
 
Promising established home in the Cove neighborhood. This home is a 3 bedroom 2.5 bath split level with nearly 2400 sq. ft of space and tons of personality. 

We’ve loved living in this quiet and beautiful neighborhood with commanding hilltop views of Three Peaks and the new LDS temple.   

Newly remodeled kitchen and dining areas, spacious family room with wood stove and brick hearth, carpet and tile throughout, also gorgeous hardwood flooring, vaulted ceiling and gas fireplace in living room, large enclosed sun room, wooden deck in back, large basement storage room and attached 2 car garage. Includes finished greenhouse and chicken coop with run. Owner will include a 1 Year home warranty. 

*Please note that we are happy to work with buyers' realtor.
data.whatILove:
This home has both personality and potential. 
It has incredible views of the surrounding area. 
We’ve loved watching Cedar City’s Independence Day fireworks from the best seat in town on the front lawn. 
Amazing neighbors. 
A sturdy greenhouse. 
Chicken coop with run and square foot gardens.
Free high speed wireless internet. 
A very large storage room which could potentially be turned into a couple of bedrooms.
The large back deck with built in seating is perfect for grilling and relaxing.
